Free cancerscreening camp heldThe New Year was ushered in by the Basavatarakam Indo-American Cancer Hospital & Research Institute with the conduct of a free cervical cancer screening camp inaugurated by Hindupur legislator Nandamuri Balakrishna, who is also its chairman.Mr. Balakrishna spent joyous moments with children fighting cancer at the Paediatric Ward, distributing fruits and other gifts to the young ones.He visited the Arogyasri wards and inaugurated an online patient feedback system, apart from inaugurating the free cancer camp.